ict shape (per element) is built **at the call site, not inside `select_cast_ids`**:\n+- `id`: character id\n+- `char_name`: same id (duplicated)\n+- spread of `all_chars[cid][\"voice\"]`, which carries: `synth`, `role`, `register` (`[lo_midi, hi_midi]`), `params` (dict: `attack`, `release`, `verb`, `dly`, plus synth-specific knobs) — fields exercised by `_play_character` at `duet_composer.py:404-429`.\n+\n+History bookkeeping at lines 399-400: `_cast_history` is updated to a flat list of ids, capped at 60.\n+\n+## Where to extend for T-016\n+\n+To attach a pre-selected sample per piece when the cast contains `sw_sampler`, two seams are plausible:\n+\n+1. **Caller-side (smaller change):** in `duet_composer._get_cast`, after the list-comp at line 396, run a `SampleSelector` over cast members whose `synth == \"sw_sampler\"` and merge a `sample` (`SampleRecord`-ish dict) field into that cast entry. `select_cast_ids` keeps its `list[str]` contract.\n+\n+2. **Planner-side (richer contract change):** add an optional `sample_selector: SampleSelector | None = None` kwarg to `select_cast_ids` and change the return type to `list[CastEntry]` (TypedDict with `id`, `voice`, optional `sample: SampleRecord`). This breaks the current `list[str]` contract and ripples into `duet_composer.py:399` (`_cast_history` extraction) and `tests/test_cast_planner.py` (5 assertions on string lists).\n+\n+Option **(1)** is the smaller change and matches the \"smallest change that satisfies the task\" rule. Option (2) better matches the PRD framing (\"attached to the cast metadata\" — `sdp/implementation-plan.md:47`).\n+\n+Either way, the metadata shape to extend is the **per-element dict built at `duet_composer.py:396`** — adding a `sample` key (and probably `voice` nested under `voice` rather than spread, for clarity) is the natural extension.\n+\n+## Open question for ESCALATIONS.md\n+\n+`SampleSelector` is owned by T-028 and does not yet exist. T-016 depends only on T-011 in the plan, which is