CHANGELOG.md:173:- Added depth-2 EMSD performance adjustment report helpers (frac-0027): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_performance.py` now exposes frozen `PerformanceEventSpec`, `PerformanceEventSnapshot`, and `PerformanceAdjustmentReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `amp_pressure_band`, `release_shape_band`, `brightness_shape_band`, `space_amount_band`, `build_performance_event_snapshot`, `build_performance_adjustment_report`, and `summarize_performance_adjustment_report` so diagnostics callers can resolve the existing live `render_adjustments_for_event(...)` path into operator-readable per-event and batch summaries. Existing `PerformanceAdjustments` fields and note-level playback behavior are preserved; `tests/test_emsd_performance_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, snapshot/live-adjustment parity, ordered aggregate role/voice/DSP/sample metadata, empty-sequence rejection, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end Theramini ducking and DSP propagation, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_performance.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:175:- Added depth-2 EMSD runtime snapshot/report helpers (frac-0026): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_runtime.py` now exposes `CANONICAL_ARC_PHASES`, `CANONICAL_DENSITY_BANDS`, frozen `EMSDPhaseSnapshot` and `EMSDRuntimeReport` dataclasses, plus pure helpers `arc_phase_index`, `arc_phase_band`, `density_pressure_band`, `build_phase_snapshot`, `build_runtime_report`, and `summarize_runtime_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a live `EMSDLiveContext` into operator-readable phase diagnostics (arc phase + index + opening/dialogue/resolution band, family/patch/sample-source identity, arc density target, max active roles, mix LUFS, density bias + calm/neutral/intense pressure band, and artistic identity statement), aggregate a sequence of snapshots into a typed runtime report (ordered phase history, canonical phase counts including zeros, canonical density-band counts, ordered distinct families/patches/sample sources, ordered arc-phase transition pairs, mean/max/min density bias rounded to 4 decimals), and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `EMSDLiveContext` fields, `build_live_emsd_context(...)`, and `composer_emsd_extras(...)` semantics are preserved so EMSD/composer/Theramini integration tests are unaffected; `tests/test_emsd_runtime_depth.py` pins canonical arc-phase ordering, opening/dialogue/resolution band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown phases), density-band cutpoints, snapshot field resolution, multi-snapshot trajectory shape, JSON round-trip stability, end-to-end snapshot/context phase agreement, empty-sequence rejection, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_runtime.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors (the smoke test for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
CHANGELOG.md:177:- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:179:- Added depth-2 score-tree report helpers (frac-0024): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` now exposes frozen `ScoreTreeSectionReport` and `ScoreTreeReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `motif_lifecycle_band`, `section_phrase_load_band`, `count_motif_lifecycle_states`, `build_score_tree_section_report`, `build_score_tree_report`, and `summarize_score_tree_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a `ScoreTree` into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-section view (id, scene, function, harmonic role/function, cadence, groove, transition intent, transform strength, target duration, phrase count, named phrase-load band, ordered de-duplicated motif refs across the section's phrases, and a `production_course_complete` flag against `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`) and tree-level view (piece id, title, form family/class/composition mode, ending family, planned duration, section/motif/phrase counts, ordered `motif_lifecycle_counts` covering every `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES` entry with zeros for absent states, ordered tuple of unreferenced motif ids, and per-section reports) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES`, `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`, `MotifNode`, `PhraseNode`, `SectionNode`, and `ScoreTree.to_dict` / `to_json` / `from_dict` / `minimal` semantics are preserved so the JSON round-trip and minimal-tree behavior continue unchanged; `tests/test_score_tree_depth.py` pins lifecycle-band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown states), phrase-load band cutpoints, canonical-only lifecycle counting, populated-tree section/tree shape, JSON round-trip stability, minimal-tree zero-state handling, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_score_tree.py` and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remain regression anchors (the latter for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
CHANGELOG.md:181:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:183:- Added depth-2 sample-lab report helpers (frac-0022): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplePlanReport` dataclass plus pure helpers `density_band`, `threshold_band`, `intensity_band`, `build_sample_plan_report`, and `summarize_sample_plan_report` so EMSD operator/diagnostics callers can resolve a `SamplePlan` together with its `sample_bank` freshness and fallback rule into one operator-readable view (source identity and capture path, refresh and freshness seconds, fallback list, cadence state, section function, transforms tuple plus count, density and named density band, buffer seconds, trigger threshold and named threshold band, intensity and named intensity band, and study focus) and emit a stable JSON-safe summary. Existing `SAMPLE_SOURCES`, `SAMPLE_SOURCE_ALIASES`, `SAMPLE_FALLBACKS`, `canonical_sample_source_name`, `sample_source`, `sample_bank`, and `plan_environmental_sampling` semantics are preserved (cadence and section-function shaping unchanged); `SamplePlan` now also carries the resolved `cadence_state` so reports can be built without re-passing it. `tests/test_sample_lab_depth.py` pins the band cutpoints, plan/bank field mirroring, alias-to-canonical bank resolution, section-function carry-through, JSON-safe summary shape, end-to-end downstream use, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sample_lab.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:185:- Added depth-2 rollout control report helpers (frac-0021): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/rollout_controls.py` now exposes frozen `RolloutFlagState` and `RolloutControlReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `flag_state`, `rollout_control_report`, and `summarize_rollout_controls` so operator/status callers can inspect the resolved SenseWeave rollout flags, raw environment values, default/defaulted/env source, enabled/disabled counts, and effective self-critique state without changing existing flag defaults. Existing `SenseWeaveFeatureFlags`, `load_feature_flags`, and downstream practice-curriculum, self-critique, and piece-commission behavior are preserved; `tests/test_rollout_controls.py` pins the new report surface, downstream end-to-end use, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_senseweave_rollout_controls.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:187:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:189:- Added depth-2 punctuation report helpers (frac-0019): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py` now exposes frozen `LanePunctuationStat` and `PunctuationReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_punctuation_stat`, `analyze_punctuation`, and `summarize_punctuation_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R6 punctuation rule once and inspect per-lane phrase-terminal outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, terminal-note count, extended-terminal count, inserted-breath count, mean terminal multiplier, mean breath milliseconds, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `PunctuationRule.apply`, and `apply_punctuation` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_punctuation_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_punctuation_depth.py` pins melody shaping, non-melodic and lane-grid-locked non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:191:- Added depth-2 duration contrast report helpers (frac-0018): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/duration_contrast.py` now exposes frozen `LaneDurationContrastStat` and `DurationContrastReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_duration_contrast_stat`, `analyze_duration_contrast`, and `summarize_duration_contrast_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R4 rule once and read back per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, step count, shaped-step count, mean rendered/original length ratio, longest-row and shortest-row indices, and an `applies` flag for role-gated and grid-locked-metadata lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `MIN_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_MULTIPLIER`, `DurationContrastRule.apply`, and `apply_duration_contrast` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_duration_contrast_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_duration_contrast_depth.py` pins per-step length-ratio counting, non-melodic and grid-locked-lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:193:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:195:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:197:- Added depth-2 render ablation helpers (frac-0015): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` now exposes frozen `AblationCase`, `AblationResult`, and `AblationSuite` dataclasses plus `rule_identifiers`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, and `summarize_ablation_suite` so CCH-010 tooling can plan single-rule or custom ablation cases, render a full-stack baseline, execute each case through the existing `ablate()` seam, and return JSON-safe operator summaries with changed/unchanged counts. Existing `ablate()` behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now pins suite planning, custom pair handling, summary output, and fractal depth >= 2, while debugger/listener-review and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:201:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:205:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:213:- Added depth-2 collaborative canvas helpers (frac-0007): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/collaborative_canvas.py` now exposes `canvas_layer_manifest`, `canvas_summary`, and `render_text_canvas` so the shared installation canvas can produce stable operator-readable layer metadata, meaningful layer/count/bounds summaries, and a deterministic fixed-size text rendering from persisted canvas state. Existing layer mutation and JSON state round-trip behavior is preserved; `tests/test_collaborative_canvas_depth.py` pins manifest ordering, summary counts and bounds, priority-based text composition, JSON round-trip rendering, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:215:- Added depth-2 character registry helpers (frac-0006): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/character_registry.py` now exposes pure helpers `voice_of`, `mode_gain_for`, `params_for`, `summarize_registry`, `voices_by_role`, and `find_voices_by_synth` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can project voice metadata, resolve per-mode gain overrides, merge voice params with caller overrides (skipping `None`-valued overrides), and inspect the registry without reaching into raw mapping shapes. Malformed `voice` entries are ignored across the diagnostic helpers, gain overrides coerce through `float()` with default fallback on non-numeric values, and bucketed/match outputs are deterministically sorted. Existing `CharacterRegistry`, `VOICE_SAMPLER_*` constants, `SAMPLER_DEFAULT_PARAMS`, and `SAMPLER_MODE_GAIN_OVERRIDES` are preserved so `cast_planner`, `duet_composer`, and `tests/test_character_registry.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_character_registry_depth.py` pins voice projection, gain override resolution, params merge with `None`-skip, registry summary histograms, role-bucket sorting, synth-match filtering, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:217:- Added depth-2 archive path layout helpers (frac-0005): `my-claw/tools/archive_paths.py` now exposes `ArchivePathLayout`, `resolve_archive_layout`, `archive_layout_summary`, and `prepare_archive_layout` so archive daemon outputs, rendered sample events, camera capture rings, and Litestream backups can be resolved and prepared as one typed storage layout while preserving the existing resolver functions. Regression coverage in `tests/test_archive_paths.py` pins root-source metadata, summary output, directory creation, legacy resolver compatibility, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:219:- Added depth-2 narrative arc helpers (frac-0004): `my-claw/tools/inner_life/narrative_arc.py` now exposes pure helpers `phase_at`, `phase_progress`, `phase_profile`, and `arc_summary` for resolving the 30-minute build/rise/climax/resolve/rest cycle without mutating an `InnerState`, with clamped position lookup, per-phase progress fractions, and stable diagnostic labels (`gathering`, `rising`, `peaking`, `resolving`, `resting`, `unknown`). `complete_cycle` now aggregates `today_events` into an `event_type_counts` histogram (bucketing missing/blank `type` keys under `unknown`), counts opinions, and records `final_phase`/`final_position` alongside the existing cycle/duration/mood/mode keys. Existing `update_arc`, `start_new_cycle`, `energy_for_phase`, and `action_weight_for_phase` semantics are preserved so `decision_engine` and `inner_life.main` callers are unaffected; `tests/test_narrative_arc_depth.py` pins phase-table boundary resolution, out-of-range clamping, within-phase progress, profile composition + neutral fallback, complete-cycle aggregation + empty-history handling, summary composition, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:221:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
