- Added depth-2 router end-to-end test coverage (frac-0108): `tests/test_router.py` now includes `RouterEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `promptclaw/router.py` public surface through one realistic routing lifecycle. The coverage exercises `agent_catalog_markdown(...)` enabled-agent rendering, `heuristic_route(...)` lead/verifier selection on a code-implementation task with confidence above the ambiguous threshold, trust-score filtering that shifts the lead away from `codex` when trust drops to zero, ambiguity detection plus clarification-question generation on a vague prompt with reduced confidence, full `route_markdown(...)` rendering of lead/verifier/task-type/confidence/reason/handoff sections (including the conditional clarification block), JSON round-tripping through `parse_route_decision(...)` with structural equality on `lead_agent`/`verifier_agent`/`task_type`/`ambiguous`/`reason`/`subtask_brief`/`confidence`, and a JSON-safe diagnostic round trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_router_depth.py` pins the router test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the router module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4653 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

